@node main "History Document."

                           Monalisa History
                             @{b}Archive 1.0b@{ub}

                           @{" Contributions "   link CONTRIBUTIONS}
                           @{" PKT Generator "   link PKTGEN}
                           @{"   Fido2UUCP   "   link FIDO2UUCP}
                           @{"   UUCP2Fido   "   link UUCP2FIDO}


        Things we plan to include in future versions of Monalisa,
        some of which are already being developed:

         x Fidonet "frontdoor" to use with TCP/IP only. Transport
           Fidonet packets through cheap Internet instead of
           telephone lines. (Almost done...)

         x Fidonet daemon. (Picasso) Allows easy implementation of
           external Areafixes, Mailinglists, Mailservers, etc...

         x NNTP support. Gate news trought your NNTP server using
           AmiTCP or AS225r2. (Working on it... Something in 10b)

         x SMTP support. Gate E-Mail trought your SMTP server.

         x German documentation. (Being translated).

         I  want  to  thank  every  Monalisa  Betatester for their
         patience  and dedication.  Monalisa would never be out as
         it  is  now  if  it wasn't for you.  The following people
         helped me with bug reports, suggestions or contributions:

          Skip Watson -- Also known as the "Weird BBS SysOp" :-)
          Eric de Jong -- The BBS colectionist. :-)
          Eric Krieger -- Thanks for the bug reports/suggestions.
          Michael van Elst -- Thanks for NNTPGet.
          Rainer Koppler -- Thanks for Convert 2.1.
          Ioannis Chatziandreou -- Offered to translate docs. to German.
          Janne Saarme -- Official distribution BBS in Finland.
          Bob Lindabury -- Great help in the early days of ML.
                           Where r you now ?

         And all the people that registered Monalisa so far.
         (Have I missed someone ? Probably yes! Sorry!)

@endnode
