@node GLOBAL1 "Global modification 1"

   The    preferences    files    are   now   stored   in   the
   MONALISA:Preferences/ directory.  This is much wiser because
   it  spares  some  memory  for  those  who have huge lists of
   conferences  to be converted and had to have the preferences
   files in RAM:  (ENV:  directory).
@endnode
@node GLOBAL2 "Global modification 2"

   All  software  should  now  run under OS2.04 or higher.  All
   known bad beaviours were corrected.
@endnode
@node GLOBAL3 "Global modification 3"

   Disabled  Ctrl-C  break  sequence during critical moments to
   prevent unlocked files and stuff like that.
@endnode
@node GLOBAL4 "Global modification 4"

   Implemented  On-Line  Help  in every GUI application.  Press
   the  HELP  Key  to  show  the correspondent document.  Also,
   fields  that have files or directories in their contents now
   have a FileRequester button.
@endnode
@node GLOBAL5 "Global modification 5"

   Every   application  now  requires  a  Keyfile  to  work  as
   registered,   thus  enabling  some  features  and  disabling
   delays.
@endnode
@node GLOBAL6 "Global modification 6"

   Everything  recompiled  with  SAS_C  6.51 and with optimized
   code.

   Version strings corrected.
@endnode
@node CONTRIBUTIONS "Monalisa Contributions"

   There  is  an  UpDate  of  the  external  program,  Convert.
   Version  2.0  was  causing  crashes  in  some configurations
   without  FAST  ram.   Thanks  to Rainer Koppler for his fast
   answers   and   his  ultra-fast  corrected  version  of  his
   excellent   utility.    Convert   2.01   is   now   in   the
   'contributions' directory.
@endnode
@node PKTGEN0902 "PKTGen Version 0.902 History"

   Updated to conform @{"Global_I" link GLOBAL1} specification.

   PKTGen  now supports pseudo-batch.  Explaining:  You can now
   specify  in  which  file you want the messages to be stored.
   PKTGen no longer has to create a .PKT file for each message.
   This   dramaticaly   improves  the  speed  of  Tossers  when
   uncompressing packets and the disk access time.

   Considerable  speed  improvement  when converting CRs to LFs
   (About 900%).  I Was using a silly routine for the job and I
   figured it when I ran PKTGen on a 68000/7Mhz machine.  ;)
@endnode
@node PKTGEN0903 "PKTGen Version 0.903 History"

   Netmail  messages  were going to BAD with most tossers.  Bug
   traced and corrected sucessfuly.

   Fixed  a  FSC  header.   Originating  zones were missing and
   consequently, netmail messages created by PKTGen would go to
   BAD with most tossers.
@endnode
@node PKTGEN0904 "PKTGen Version 0.904 History"

   Fully implemented Type-2 packet headers proposed in FSC0039.
   Known  problems  with  some  tossers just simply disapeared.
   Thanks to Skip Watson for his contribution withs FSC and FTS
   files and Betatesting.

   Fixed a minor bug that was generating equal MSGIDs from time
   to time causing messages to go to BAD with most mailers.
@endnode
@node PKTGEN0905 "PKTGen Version 0.905 History"

   Improved  MSGID  generation  routine  to  prevent accidental
   DUPES.  Now based in system clock to microseconds precision.
@endnode
@node PKTGEN0906 "PKTGen Version 0.906 History"

   Updated to conform @{"Global_V" link GLOBAL5} specification.
@endnode
@node PKTGEN0907 "PKTGen Version 0.907 History"

   Added   two   command   line   arguments.    REPLYADDR   and
   NOREPLYADDR.   If  used,  will  cause PKTGen to add a kludge
   called  "REPLYADDR"  with the Internet E-Mail address of the
   origin  user.   There  is also a new line with the REPLYADDR
   default in the configuration files.
@endnode
@node PKTGEN0908 "PKTGen Version 0.908 History"

   Fixed  two Type 2 Packet problems.  4D Point addresses would
   not always be stored correctly and the binary Date field was
   always generated wrong.
@endnode
@node PKTGEN0909 "PKTGen Version 0.909 History"

   Added the MSGPRIVATE flag.
@endnode
@node FIDO2UUCP0902 "Fido2UUCP Version 0.902 History"

   Updated to conform @{"Global_I" link GLOBAL1} specification.

   Updated to conform @{"Global_II" link GLOBAL2} specification.

   Updated to conform @{"Global_III" link GLOBAL3} specification.

   Configuration GUI tottaly redesigned.

   Added  individual distribution parameter for each conference
   rather than being "world" for all.

   Added  individual  convertion  tables  for  each conference.
   These  are  used  by  "Convert  2.0"  with the permission of
   Rainer  Koppler, the author, to convert the charsets between
   diferent systems.

   Added LOG file support.

   Added  WordWrap  routine to the Tosser so that the long text
   lines  usually  found  in  the Fidonet packets are correctly
   converted to the Usenet articles.

   Improved  Tosser  performance  by optimizing frequently used
   functions.

   Better  error  handling.   Changed  from  exec AllocMem() to
   SAS_C  malloc()  to  prevent  unfreed  memory  at  premature
   breaks.
@endnode
@node FIDO2UUCP0903 "Fido2UUCP Version 0.903 History"

   Major speed improvements in the Tosser.

   Again,  a concept review made me change a lot of things with
   Fido2UUCP.   Added a few fields in the configuration module:
   "RNews  Path"  and  "LocalHost  Name"  to make Fido2UUCP not
   dependant  from  AmigaUUCP  standard  paths and make it more
   compatible with other UUCP packages.

   Tosser  no  longer writes articles directly into the UUNEWS:
   hierarchy.   Instead, it will create a temporary RNews Batch
   file  and  use  the  RNews  command to unpack it.  This also
   increases compatibility with diferent UUCP packages.

   Tosser  now  supports  private replies from the Usenet side.
   This  is  archieved  by  converting the Fidonet address to a
   Internet       address       in       the      form      of:
   Test.Name@p1.f2.n362.z2.fido.org  thus  using  the  internet
   gateway for E-Mail.
@endnode
@node FIDO2UUCP0904 "Fido2UUCP Version 0.904 History"

   Implemented  rnews header correctly.  The byte count of each
   article  is  now  present.   This  was  set to 0 in previous
   versions.

   Now removing Tear Lines together with Origin Lines.

   The  "Path:"  field is now the first after the rnews header.
   This   makes   CNews  RNews  work  correctly  with  Monalisa
   generated batches.

   Removed  a minor bug that was printing the last line of each
   article twice in the temporary batchfile.

   Removed a bug that would print some trash to the screen when
   the  EchoMail  was not in the convertion list, thus going to
   the "junk" Newsgroup.
@endnode
@node FIDO2UUCP0905 "Fido2UUCP Version 0.905 History"

   Updated to conform @{"Global_IV" link GLOBAL4} specification.

   Added another field.  It's called 'E-Mail Gatename'.  Can be
   defined  for  each  conference.  His objective is to let the
   system  administrator  define  the  path  for private E-Mail
   coming  from  sites  that  are  fed  with  converted Fidonet
   Echomail.   Default  used to be "fidonet.org" but as you can
   read in the documentation, there are many reasons not to use
   this so often.  This is the first step to full E-Mail gating
   implementation.   Thanks  to  Skip  Walter  for his precious
   explanations.

   * WARNING *
   Previous preference files are no longer compatible with this
   version.   You must update them.  With other updates this is
   no  longer  a  problem  since  I've created unused space for
   future use.
@endnode
@node FIDO2UUCP0906 "Fido2UUCP Version 0.906 History"

   Fido2UUCP  configuration  program has two sections now.  One
   for   Echomail   and   another   for  E-Mail,  that  is  now
   implemented.   The  E-Mail  window  has  two  Listviews that
   prevent  unauthorized  use  of the Gateway by defining which
   systems can and which systems can't use the E-Mail service.

   Three  new  fields  and  two  new  flags.   'Outbound  Dir',
   'Inbound  Dir',  'Reply  Message  File', 'Scan Echomail' and
   'Reply Bad Messages'.  Read documentation for details.

   Implemented BusyWindow() correctly.

   Improved configuration save routines performance.
@endnode
@node FIDO2UUCP0907 "Fido2UUCP Version 0.907 History"

    Implemented Netmail gating.  (Tosser)

    Removed  a  nasty "bug" that would cause the Work Directory
    to  stay  locked  after  Tosser quit and thus impossible to
    remove  without having to reset the system.  Hard to trace!
    Uff!
@endnode
@node FIDO2UUCP0908 "Fido2UUCP Version 0.908 History"

    Better packet handling.

    Corrected Version String format.

    Implemented  mutual  exclusion in Tosser.  Only one Tosser
    may run at a time.
@endnode
@node FIDO2UUCP0909 "Fido2UUCP Version 0.909 History"

    Some ^A lines were escaping to the "filter".  Fixed!

    Implemented Time Zone variable.

    Implemented  a  new  way  to  gate NetMail to Internet.  If
    TOSSER  gets  any  NetMail sent to UUCP, it will try to get
    the  destination  address  in  the  first  message line and
    proceed.     Suggested   by   Skip   Watson   to   increase
    compatibility with other Gateway software.

    Improved Tosser to handle TrapToss packets better.

    Implemented Bcc: and Cc: lines.

    Rewrote some Fido2UUCP documentation.  The 'Local Hostname'
    explanation  was  wrong  (I got confused when I first wrote
    it).   'Local  Hostname'  was changed to 'Gateway Hostname'
    and documentation was corrected.

    Fixed a rmail problem. Thanks Skip!

    Lots  of  other  improvements and minor problems corrected.
    Hopefuly this will be the last version before the release.
@endnode
@node FIDO2UUCP0910 "Fido2UUCP Version 0.910 History"

   Just when I thought I could release Tosser...  ;)

   A   Bug   interpreting  the  INTL:   kludge  was  corrected.
   Sometimes,  the  FromAddress was replace by your net address
   because of this.

   Updated to conform @{"Global_V" link GLOBAL5} specification.
@endnode
@node FIDO2UUCP0911 "Fido2UUCP Version 0.911 History"

   Added more routines and improved existing ones.  Tosser will
   now  virtualy  toss  well type 2 Packets from any machine or
   any  system.   It  will even try and sucessfuly toss corrupt
   packets.   Widely tested with many platforms.  Thanks to all
   Monalisa  betatesters  for  loads of "not-so-common" packets
   for me to analise.

   Fixed  a  another little path problem when using compressors
   other than "lha", like "unzip".
@endnode
@node UUCP2FIDO0903 "UUCP2Fido Version 0.903 History"

   Updated to conform @{"Global_I" link GLOBAL1} specification.

   Updated to conform @{"Global_II" link GLOBAL2} specification.

   Updated to conform @{"Global_III" link GLOBAL3} specification.

   Added individual Origin Line for each conference.

   Better  error  handling.   Changed  from  exec AllocMem() to
   SAS_C  malloc()  to  prevent  unfreed  memory  at  premature
   breaks.
@endnode
@node UUCP2FIDO0904 "UUCP2Fido Version 0.904 History"

   Wrote some new concepts down in paper and thought about them
   for  hours.   Finally  got with a solution that would change
   UUCP2Fido  drasticaly.   UUCP2Fido will no longer search for
   articles in the UUNEWS:  hierarchy.  Instead, it will work a
   lot  Fido2UUCP  and  decompress bundles for a fake system in
   UUSPOOL:.   This is much more dificult to implement from the
   programmer's point but increases compatibility with diferent
   configurations,  and  is  probably easier to understand from
   the user's point of view.

   Redraw  a  new  GUI  for  the  configuration  program.  This
   includes   two   new   options:   Gateway  System  Name  and
   Decompressor.

   Added  two  more  configurable  arguments.  One is the 'From
   Address'  where  you  can specify the address from which the
   converted  .PKTs  are  coming  from  and  the other is 'Work
   Directory'  where  you can tell UUCP2Fido to work with, some
   times,  huge  data  files.   This  used to be T:  but in low
   memory configurations there might be some problems.
@endnode
@node UUCP2FIDO0906 "UUCP2Fido Version 0.906 History"

   Well,  so  many  new  things  that I won't even mention them
   here.   Just  see  the  docs.   E-Mail  gating  is  working.
   Crosspostings   are   handled.    Uncompressed  batches  are
   handled.   Spliting  big  articles feature was added.  Etc..
   Etc...

   Updated to conform @{"Global_V" link GLOBAL5} specification.
@endnode
@node UUCP2FIDO0907 "UUCP2Fido Version 0.907 History"

   *WARNING*  you  must  update  your  configuration  file from
   V0.906.  See the /update directory for details.

   Updated to conform @{"Global_VI" link GLOBAL6} specification.

   Crosspostings   are   *really*  handled  now.   It's  really
   impossible  to  handle crossposting 100% because there is no
   way  to  know which is the group to gate from the Newsgroup:
   line.   Well, at least now articles are not lost.  UUCP2Fido
   will scan the entire line for a valid newsgroup and not only
   the first as it did in V0.906.

   There's a better filter for article headers.  Very flexible.
   See UUCP2Fido configuration program.

   The   Max.Mesg.Size  option,  when  enabled,  will  not  cut
   articles  in  the  middle  of  a  line.   Because of this, I
   suggest   that  you  give  a  200  bytes  tolerance  in  the
   Max.Mesg.Size value.

   Splitted   articles   will   have  a  better  subject  line.
   [5/1]...[5/2]...  etc.  This will cause not so smart tossers
   to  take  the  message  as good and don't throw it away as a
   dupe.

   Splited is now Splitted :-)

   A BUG that was causing faulty PKTs with only one NULL at the
   end was corrected.  Thanks Eric!

   There's  a  new  field  in  the configuration program called
   PKTGen  flags.   You  can  add special PKTGen flags for each
   created  packet.   Example:  MSGPRIVATE flag is necessary if
   you are working with XMail from E!  (till version 1.21).

   Possible harmless enforcer hit removed.
@endnode
